    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 2000 4000 and 8000 MODELS BUILT OCTOBER 1, 1998 AND AFTER -
        SPEEDOMETER/TACHOMETER, GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - 9800 - Troubleshooting - MECHANICAL ODOMETER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>MECHANICAL ODOMETER</title>
        <para>Perform the test in the following chart if the Odometer doesn't work.</para>
        <table id="t0824504">
            <title>Mechanical Odometer Test Chart</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.54in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.26in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove Speedometer/ Tachometer module and make sure the odometer is plugged securely
                                into the module circuit board.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Good Con- nection.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Connect and Retest.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect odometer lead and momentarily apply 12 Volts across the odometer leads.
                                Each time power is applied, the odometer should increment.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Odometer leads.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Odometer increments.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace Speedometer/ Tachometer module.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace odometer.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcproc>
